flavorText: This very forgetful Pokémon will wait for a new order from its Trainer even though it already has one.
Many people believe that, deep in the forest where Tranquill live, there is a peaceful place where there is no war.
Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females' flying abilities surpass those of the males.
He was the partner of Tim's father, Harry, who has gone missing. This Pikachu loves the dark coffee at the Hi-Hat Cafe.
It appears when it senses an impending natural disaster. As a result, it was mistaken as a doom bringer.
Using the feelers on its ears, it can tell how someone is feeling or when an egg might hatch.
The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.
It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.
While it's an amiable Pokémon, if you touch it unexpectedly, it will heat up its body in an instant, and you'll be burned.
Its stomach takes up most of its long torso. It's a big eater, so the amount Trainers have to spend on its food is no laughing matter.
Skilled in deduction, he's a self-proclaimed "great detective." His detective hat is his trademark.
Although it wasn't originally found in Alola, this Pokémon was brought over a long time ago when there was a huge Rattata outbreak.
It normally spends its time meditating in the treetops. It throws Poké Balls and gives other Pokémon orders as it pleases.
A Pokémon weapon developed for a specific mission, it went berserk during an experiment, so it was cryogenically frozen.
It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.
This is its form once it has awakened and evolved. Freed from its heavy mask, its speed is greatly increased.
It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.
A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this Pokémon.
Magearna, with its metallic body, is an artificial Pokémon created 500 years ago by humans.
It stays asleep from the moment it's born. When it falls into a deep sleep, it stops moving altogether.
Using psychokinesis gives it a headache, so it normally passes the time spacing out and doing as little as possible.
It grows close to others easily and is also easily spoiled. The disparity between its face and its actions makes many young people wild about it.
It has the power to travel across time, but it is said to appear only in peaceful times.
The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.
They show off their Poké Ball caps to lure prey, but very few Pokémon are fooled by this.
When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being's entire body will be overflowing with power.
This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog, it came to be both feared and revered.
It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.
It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings, causing a blizzard to chase offenders away.
It looks somehow pained as it rages around in search of light, which serves as its energy. It's apparently from another world.
When it is resolute, it body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.
What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.
Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokémon is spoken of in legends.
Its DNA is said to contain the genetic codes of all Pokémon, so it can use all kinds of techniques.
Its nature is to store up electricity. Forests where nests of Pikachu live are dangerous, since the trees are so often struck by lightning.
Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.
It's so popular with the elderly that there's a magazine devoted to this Pokémon. Fans obsess over the particular length and angle of its arms.
It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during the nights of the new moon.
It has an organ that generates electricity in its abdomen. It concentrates energy in its strong jaws and fires off powerful jolts of electricity.
It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.
It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.
This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.
It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.
It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.
It knows the forest inside and out. If it comes across a wounded Pokémon, Oranguru will gather medicinal herbs to treat it.
